      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the sound is piercing and sounds like metal on metal, you need to check the hardware and clearances, as this suggests more than just a bedding-in issue. First, ensure the caliper hardware (like the slide pins or anti-rattle clips) are clean, lubricated, and moving freely. Also, visually inspect the rotor surface for any deep scoring or uneven wear patterns, which could indicate a serious mechanical issue or improper installation.",
